 Google Play Store Analysis

 📌 Objective
The objective of this project is to perform a comprehensive Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) of the Google Play Store ecosystem by cleaning real-world data, analyzing app categories, ratings, installs, pricing trends, and conducting sentiment analysis on user reviews.

---

🛠️ Tech Stack
- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn
- Plotly
- TextBlob
- Jupyter Notebook

---

 📂 Dataset
This project uses two publicly available datasets from Kaggle:
1. googleplaystore.csv
2. googleplaystore_user_reviews.csv

---
 📋 Project Workflow

 ✔ Data Loading
- Loaded Google Play Store Apps dataset
- Loaded User Reviews dataset

 ✔ Data Cleaning
- Removed duplicate records
- Handled missing values
- Fixed incorrect data types
- Cleaned Installs column
- Converted Price to numeric values
- Processed App Size column

   ✔ Exploratory Data Analysis
- App distribution by category
- Rating distribution
